                <note type="abstract">An edition and English translation of Yefet’s Judaeo-Arabic translation and commentary on Daniel, based on 9 Mss., two of which are written in Arabic script, though these two are rather fragmentary. Margoliouth nonetheless transcribes the entirety of his edited text, which is attested primarily in Hebrew-script Mss., into Arabic script since he considers all the Hebrew-script Mss. to have derived from one Arabic-script archetype (pp. xi–xii). Includes an introduction by Margoliouth. See the reviews of H. Hirschfeld in ZDMG 45 (1891): 330–36 {https://www.zotero.org/groups/538215/biblia_arabica/items/itemKey/QH876XZF}; and L.M. Simmons in JQR 2 (1890): 186–88 {https://www.zotero.org/groups/538215/biblia_arabica/items/itemKey/Y5GQXIFM}.</note>
